WEBVTT

00:05.580 --> 00:08.580
Our time capsule 
was buried in 1987.

00:08.600 --> 00:11.760
The year the DOW closed
above 2000 for the first time.

00:11.800 --> 00:14.740
Reagan told Gorbachev to
tear down the Berlin Wall.

00:14.750 --> 00:18.210
You had a huge crush 
on LaToya Jackson.

00:18.260 --> 00:19.100
I did.

00:19.130 --> 00:20.910
You can't complain,Stinson.

00:20.920 --> 00:22.380
You married the 
head cheerleader.

00:22.410 --> 00:23.620
Lucky I did.

00:23.910 --> 00:26.890
And now we have a wonderful kid
who's a senior,right here at Foothill.

00:26.930 --> 00:28.690
Alex,take a bow.

00:29.850 --> 00:35.850
Anyhow,we're here today to open the
time capsule that we buried 20 years ago,

00:35.870 --> 00:39.810
so we can see who we were and how the
heck we all got to where we are today.

00:39.900 --> 00:41.140
Found it!

00:44.010 --> 00:45.190
Twenty years...

00:45.200 --> 00:46.540
Do you even remember
what you put in there?

00:46.560 --> 00:49.360
No. A bad perm and pink
leg warmers,probably.

00:50.770 --> 00:52.370
Here we go!

00:57.340 --> 00:58.740
God! That is vile!

00:58.770 --> 00:59.830
Oh,what the hell,Bill?

00:59.850 --> 01:01.350
I thought you said the
thing was watertight?

01:01.370 --> 01:04.060
It should've been,and it's Gil,not Bill.

01:04.450 --> 01:06.110
Let's see what we've got here.

01:13.890 --> 01:15.340
What is it?!

01:18.440 --> 01:20.170
Now this is a sweet field.

01:20.180 --> 01:22.000
This is what I'm talking about. Right?

01:22.020 --> 01:23.450
I mean,it's nothing like ours,

01:23.470 --> 01:26.520
but,hey,that didn't stop me
from being MVP my senior year.

01:26.540 --> 01:28.030
Got the trophy,touchdown!

01:28.070 --> 01:32.520
In certain tribes,in the African
subcontinent,piercings serve as a reminder,

01:32.530 --> 01:36.900
like your trophy,of the power and
agility,which has since faded away.

01:36.930 --> 01:38.360
What do you mean,fade away?

01:38.370 --> 01:39.010
Time out.

01:39.040 --> 01:40.350
Can we just concentrate on the case?

01:40.370 --> 01:41.090
What do we got here?

01:41.130 --> 01:42.540
We were all gathered for the opening.

01:42.560 --> 01:46.810
We had no idea that
that thing was in there.

01:48.100 --> 01:49.340
That is rank.

01:49.370 --> 01:52.410
I was just expecting to
see my 10,000 Maniacs album.

01:52.430 --> 01:53.940
That was not there.

01:53.970 --> 01:54.580
Who are you?

01:54.610 --> 01:55.770
I'm Gil Bates.

01:55.800 --> 01:56.900
I sealed it myself.

01:56.920 --> 01:59.490
I used a propylene seal
and industrial bolt lags.

01:59.500 --> 02:03.880
Adolescent,Caucasian
male,late teens,early 20s.

02:03.910 --> 02:08.039
All right,so,what do you say we just pack it
all up and ship it back to the Jeffersonian?

02:08.060 --> 02:09.979
Oh,I'm sorry. That's not a good idea.

02:10.000 --> 02:13.810
You see,the water has compromised the
structural integrity of the case,so...

02:13.820 --> 02:15.220
Well,will you look at this,Bones.

02:15.240 --> 02:17.280
Another nerd for your squint squad.

02:17.310 --> 02:18.270
- Drill.
- Drill.

02:18.290 --> 02:20.520
Drill? Whoa,wait a second. You're
going to drill it right here?

02:20.540 --> 02:22.470
What about taking it
all back to Jeffersonian?

02:22.500 --> 02:23.470
Tub.

