05:08.580 --> 05:10.350
I ran a sample of the sludge.

05:10.390 --> 05:11.490
Organic matter.

05:11.520 --> 05:12.950
Or you could call him "Roger."

05:12.990 --> 05:14.960
Oh,come on,when 
you can ladle someone,

05:14.990 --> 05:17.100
he's a little less than
a person,don't you think?

05:17.170 --> 05:17.680
Fine.

05:17.720 --> 05:21.350
I took a sample of Roger,ran it
through the mass spectrometer.

05:21.390 --> 05:22.500
You'll never guess what I found.

05:22.510 --> 05:24.880
Traces of an unidentified
organophosphate.

05:24.890 --> 05:26.230
- Nerve gas?
- Very good.

05:26.260 --> 05:27.670
I'll break down the rest chemicals now.

05:27.700 --> 05:30.920
The victim also had a
peri-mortem fracture in his wrist.

05:30.960 --> 05:34.900
There are indications of a grade-two
acromioclavicular joint separation.

05:34.930 --> 05:36.590
But it was certainly not lethal.

05:36.630 --> 05:37.410
I've seen it before.

05:37.430 --> 05:40.770
Someone twisted the victim's
arm behind his back,forcefully.

05:40.790 --> 05:42.410
So,what,he got beat
up for his lunch money?

05:42.440 --> 05:45.230
Violent students are the
hallmark of a schoolyard.

05:45.260 --> 05:47.810
I speak from experience.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.250
However,these fractures on his
ribs might predate high school.

05:52.260 --> 05:55.950
So...he might've had
some trouble at home.

06:01.970 --> 06:05.740
I don't understand,Mr. Dillon,why
you never reported your son missing.

06:05.790 --> 06:08.750
His mother told me 
that Roger ran away.

06:08.780 --> 06:11.940
You weren't concerned that your
son never contacted you again?

06:11.960 --> 06:13.360
He didn't live with
me,he didn't want to.

06:13.390 --> 06:15.820
Because of the physical abuse?

06:16.110 --> 06:19.140
Yeah,I was a drinker in those days.

06:19.160 --> 06:22.310
And I understood why he
wanted to just write me off.

06:22.330 --> 06:23.340
But I cared about him.

06:23.370 --> 06:24.360
I was sick.

06:24.390 --> 06:26.330
When was the last 
time you saw Roger?

06:26.350 --> 06:29.240
It was night of his
high school graduation.

06:29.270 --> 06:32.930
He came over here,afterwards,
asking me for money,a lot.

06:32.940 --> 06:35.620
You threw him out of the house with
his arm twisted behind his back.

06:35.650 --> 06:36.850
I swear,he...

06:36.860 --> 06:38.990
he got up and he walked away.

06:39.040 --> 06:41.320
Now this was 20 years ago.

06:41.330 --> 06:43.140
What's this all about?

06:43.180 --> 06:45.280
Roger is dead,Mr. Dillon.

06:45.300 --> 06:49.280
His remains were found yesterday.

06:50.170 --> 06:52.470
Oh...God...

06:52.510 --> 06:53.910
Found him at the high school.

06:53.950 --> 06:57.420
He had been in a time
capsule for 20 years.

06:58.680 --> 07:01.340
Any idea why he 
needed the money?

07:02.010 --> 07:02.990
Wouldn't say.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.430
Guess it was so 
he could run away.

07:06.280 --> 07:08.310
You should talk to Gil.

07:08.340 --> 07:10.310
He was Roger's best friend.

07:10.330 --> 07:11.190
Gil Bates?

07:11.220 --> 07:12.270
Yeah.

07:12.300 --> 07:13.360
That's the Tech Town guy?

07:13.400 --> 07:16.320
Yeah. They did everything together.

07:16.410 --> 07:18.050
We'll be in touch.

07:20.300 --> 07:22.090
I'm different now.

07:22.920 --> 07:24.090
I'm sober.

07:24.130 --> 07:26.850
I never... I never wanted to hurt him.

07:26.880 --> 07:28.930
I loved Roger.

07:31.150 --> 07:32.590
Right.

07:37.220 --> 07:40.140
The kid basically
melted into all of this.

07:40.170 --> 07:43.200
I should be able to pull more
chemical traces off the artifacts

07:43.240 --> 07:45.100
to I.D. the organophosphate on him.

07:45.130 --> 07:47.530
- Beta--  -
St.Elmo's Fire.

07:47.550 --> 07:49.360
It's on the list.

07:49.750 --> 07:51.000
One yearbook.

07:51.010 --> 07:52.970
Foothill High School,1987.

07:53.000 --> 07:53.580
Check.

07:53.610 --> 07:54.820
Dehydrate and scan.

07:54.860 --> 07:55.940
"Have a great summer."

07:55.950 --> 07:57.300
"Don't ever change."

07:57.320 --> 07:58.210
Remember those days?

07:58.240 --> 08:00.050
I remember getting
grounded every weekend.

08:00.070 --> 08:02.280
So many rules to break,
so little time...

08:02.310 --> 08:03.570
You were the nerd fantasy.

08:03.590 --> 08:04.820
I was all about Barbie.

08:04.840 --> 08:06.370
She was my first anatomy lesson.

08:06.380 --> 08:08.250
I was confused for years.

08:08.290 --> 08:09.190
What about Ken?

08:09.220 --> 08:10.760
I felt so sorry for him.

08:10.780 --> 08:13.330
Floppy disk the size of a dinner plate.

08:13.350 --> 08:14.180
Bingo,baby.

08:14.210 --> 08:16.010
The disk is not on the list.

08:16.030 --> 08:17.670
Wow,what are you?

08:17.700 --> 08:18.590
A term paper?

08:18.630 --> 08:19.830
Launch codes?

08:19.860 --> 08:20.640
We need to pull the data.

08:20.660 --> 08:22.470
Do you think you're up to it?

08:22.520 --> 08:23.990
I can try.

08:24.380 --> 08:25.590
A hockey skate.

08:25.650 --> 08:27.780
And it looks like it's signed.

08:27.810 --> 08:28.640
Check on the skate.

08:28.670 --> 08:31.520
It belonged to some
jock named John Adamson.

08:31.560 --> 08:33.150
A can of New Coke.

08:33.179 --> 08:35.980
Definitely an '80's plot
to destabilize the country.

08:36.010 --> 08:37.130
Another check.

08:37.169 --> 08:38.400
And a pocket watch.

08:38.429 --> 08:40.780
The watch is not on the list.

08:43.870 --> 08:45.090
It's a Wallingham.

08:45.120 --> 08:45.970
It's nice.

08:46.000 --> 08:49.110
A computer disk and a pocket watch?

08:49.140 --> 08:50.630
What was our little geek into?

08:50.650 --> 08:52.310
It's dry.

08:52.400 --> 08:54.410
This is a good watch.

08:54.720 --> 08:56.040
Some kind of residue.

08:56.090 --> 08:57.780
Could it help I.D. the poison?

08:57.800 --> 08:59.150
Let me at it.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.740
Roger's father had no
trouble getting physical.

09:05.760 --> 09:09.250
So why would he resort to poisoning
his son with a nerve agent?

09:09.260 --> 09:10.840
What sort of teenager were you,Bones?

09:10.870 --> 09:13.310
He did have a series of odd jobs.

09:13.330 --> 09:15.620
Perhaps he procured the
poison from one of them.

09:15.640 --> 09:20.010
Come on,you have to have at least one
good story before you pasted on a lab coat.

09:20.020 --> 09:21.470
I was busy,studying.

09:21.490 --> 09:25.110
And in all those hours of studying,you
never came across one hormone?

09:25.130 --> 09:28.110
Fine,there was one boy.

09:29.970 --> 09:31.910
Andy Pfleuger.

09:31.970 --> 09:34.690
He was the varsity lacrosse captain.

09:34.710 --> 09:38.800
Did you kiss the
varsity lacrosse captain?

09:38.830 --> 09:41.070
I was weighing the pros and cons...

09:41.130 --> 09:43.470
when he became my Secret Santa.

09:43.490 --> 09:44.870
I thought you hated Secret Santa.

09:44.900 --> 09:48.080
Yes,because he taped
the gift to my locker.

09:48.100 --> 09:49.850
Everyone saw it.

09:50.370 --> 09:51.930
Teenagers can be cruel.

09:51.960 --> 09:53.240
What was it?

09:53.280 --> 09:54.260
It doesn't matter.

09:54.310 --> 09:55.970
Come on,Bones.

09:55.980 --> 09:57.300
You promise not to laugh?

09:57.320 --> 09:59.190
Listen,I'm your partner.

09:59.740 --> 10:01.470
It was a Brainy Smurf.

10:01.810 --> 10:03.560
You said you wouldn't laugh.

10:03.570 --> 10:04.860
I'm not laughing.

10:04.880 --> 10:05.850
Brainy Smurf,huh?

10:05.880 --> 10:06.950
Well,it was deliberate.

10:06.980 --> 10:09.650
He knew I wanted Smurfette.

10:10.270 --> 10:11.870
Okay,it's clear you find this amusing.

10:11.890 --> 10:13.630
I'm not laughing.

10:13.650 --> 10:15.410
I'm not.

10:16.270 --> 10:17.500
What?

10:18.230 --> 10:21.320
You know,Angel was right--
you were one ofthoseguys.

10:21.360 --> 10:22.260
What?

10:22.870 --> 10:24.680
One of what guys?

10:26.080 --> 10:28.560
That was Roger in the time capsule?

10:29.580 --> 10:31.100
I saw his skull.

10:31.130 --> 10:33.130
Oh,my God,I saw his skull.

10:33.410 --> 10:35.940
He's been there since 1987.

10:35.950 --> 10:37.730
No,Roger took off. He left a note.

10:37.760 --> 10:38.860
A note?

10:38.880 --> 10:40.310
Graduation night,he left his mom a note,

10:40.350 --> 10:42.450
saying that he hated it
here and he was running away.

10:42.470 --> 10:44.550
Yeah,and he went to his
father's house to ask for money.

10:44.580 --> 10:45.500
Do you know why?

10:45.530 --> 10:48.140
All I knew was what his mom said
was in the note he left,so...

10:48.180 --> 10:51.040
Gil,his mother was dead,and
his father never saw it,so...

10:51.080 --> 10:54.860
So,you're the only connection
we have to the note.

10:55.830 --> 11:02.550
It said,uh,you know that he
couldn't be around his dad anymore.

11:02.600 --> 11:04.420
Or the kids at school.

11:04.520 --> 11:05.890
They picked on him.

11:06.440 --> 11:08.630
They used to pick on me,too.

11:09.840 --> 11:11.960
I guess,he just couldn't take it.

11:13.900 --> 11:16.250
Why wouldn't he have
just asked for help?

11:16.990 --> 11:19.010
He was my best friend.

11:20.920 --> 11:23.320
I always thought that I'd see him again.

11:25.390 --> 11:27.520
I can't believe I'll
never see him again.

11:35.690 --> 11:40.220
All right,I found several denim cotton
fibers on both the gold watch and the floppy,

11:40.240 --> 11:44.610
matching what's left of the victim's
classic acid wash '80s jeans.

11:44.630 --> 11:48.340
That places the watch and the disk inside
the victim's pocket at the time of his murder.

11:48.370 --> 11:50.770
I tested the residue
inside the watch casing.

11:50.810 --> 11:53.160
Pure crystalline tropane alkaloid.

11:53.180 --> 11:55.470
Roger Dillon had a pocket
watch full of cocaine?

11:55.520 --> 11:58.690
It's soMiami Vice,I
could roll up my sleeves.

11:58.710 --> 12:04.020
The FBI sent us the files of everyone
connected to the school who had a record.

12:04.080 --> 12:07.230
Mostly petty theft,D.U.I.s,that
sort of thing.

12:08.260 --> 12:09.460
Darwin Banks.

12:09.480 --> 12:11.400
Teacher at Foothill High.

12:11.430 --> 12:15.750
Arrested in a schoolwide
drug bust,June 12,1987.

12:15.770 --> 12:18.190
That's two days after Roger disappeared.

12:18.230 --> 12:19.660
And Roger need money.

12:19.690 --> 12:23.480
Looks like our young geek might've
been killed over a drug deal.

12:34.970 --> 12:36.870
Do you rember Roger Dillon?

12:36.900 --> 12:38.510
Foothill High,right?

12:39.140 --> 12:40.810
I was his science teacher.

12:40.860 --> 12:41.950
Smart kid.

12:41.980 --> 12:42.880
He could've taught the class.

12:42.910 --> 12:44.460
Now he's dead.

12:44.910 --> 12:48.120
We found him stuffed into
Foothill's time capsule.

12:48.160 --> 12:50.630
Been there since 1987.

12:50.690 --> 12:51.530
God...

12:51.580 --> 12:57.690
And it says here in the yearbook that you were
the faculty advisor to the time capsule committee.

12:57.740 --> 12:58.940
You gotta be kidding.

12:58.970 --> 13:03.110
I usually don't joke around when
a 17- year-old boy's been murdered.

13:04.360 --> 13:06.420
Found evidence of cocaine on him.

13:06.440 --> 13:07.690
Roger? No.

13:07.720 --> 13:09.130
That kid was clean.

13:09.160 --> 13:12.980
The only way he got high was sitting
in front of his computer writing code.

13:13.030 --> 13:17.430
Right,so help me out here,because in '87 you
were arrested at the high school for dealing.

13:17.460 --> 13:18.390
I wasn't dealing.

13:18.410 --> 13:19.680
I was just out of college.

13:19.690 --> 13:20.970
I had two joints on me.

13:21.010 --> 13:22.800
And four ounces in your apartment.

13:22.830 --> 13:24.220
I was 23.

13:24.230 --> 13:26.790
We all do crazy stuff when we're kids.

13:26.820 --> 13:28.310
Exactly.

13:29.700 --> 13:32.550
I have my own business
now,a wife and two kids.

13:32.580 --> 13:35.150
I'm in the Rotary Club for God's sake.

13:35.180 --> 13:36.770
Well,we know that Roger needed money.

13:36.790 --> 13:40.750
Maybe he started dealing for
you,and he wanted a bigger payout,

13:40.770 --> 13:42.460
threatened to turn you
in if he didn't get it,

13:42.480 --> 13:45.000
so you killed him?

13:45.030 --> 13:47.400
I didn't kill him and
Roger didn't rat me out.

13:47.430 --> 13:53.230
It was Adamson,John Adamson,an
entitled ass even at 17.

13:53.250 --> 13:55.890
I caught him cheating
and the next thing I know,

13:55.910 --> 13:58.910
the cops are knocking
on my classroom door.

13:58.920 --> 14:01.720
He just wanted to discredit
me,so he could retake the test.

14:01.760 --> 14:05.920
Right. So you're the victim
with four ounces of weed?

14:06.260 --> 14:10.470
Can you confirm your
whereabouts on June 14,1987?

14:10.520 --> 14:15.750
If I'm such a big drug-dealing
liar,why would I tell you the truth?

14:15.780 --> 14:19.550
Because you don't want to go to
jail for killing Roger Dillon.

14:23.430 --> 14:26.460
Come on,Sweets,just come on,you've
done a lot of psychological profiling.

14:26.490 --> 14:28.550
The case is 20 years
old,we just need some help.

14:28.580 --> 14:30.840
That's not why we're
here today,Agent Booth.

14:30.860 --> 14:32.870
This hour is for you and Dr. Brennan.

14:32.890 --> 14:35.280
Oh,she's not gonna mind; it's
only gonna take five minutes,okay?

14:35.310 --> 14:36.510
1987.

14:36.530 --> 14:40.700
Suburban kid is killed and
stuffed into a time capsule.

14:40.730 --> 14:42.230
Fascinating,right?

14:42.260 --> 14:45.410
What kind of person would do that?

14:45.930 --> 14:49.750
So have any conflicts or issues
arisen since our last session?

14:49.780 --> 14:52.900
Well... Bones and I
are doing just great.

14:52.910 --> 14:55.330
You look angry,Dr. Brennan.

14:57.130 --> 15:03.260
I told Agent Booth a private story
about my childhood and he laughed.

15:03.870 --> 15:05.100
What?

