in that story,Booth.

28:54.360 --> 28:56.710
You don't even know what
public humiliation is.

28:56.720 --> 28:58.070
- Hi.
- Hi.

28:58.080 --> 29:00.970
Uh,Ms. Stinson,
Special Agent Booth,uh...

29:00.980 --> 29:03.240
Was your name Janelle
Brown in high school?

29:03.250 --> 29:04.040
Yes.

29:04.050 --> 29:06.400
Mind if we come in and
ask you a few questions?

29:06.410 --> 29:09.080
Of course,yeah. Come in.

29:10.850 --> 29:12.300
Look at her.

29:12.640 --> 29:14.570
I wish I was Janelle Brown again.

29:14.580 --> 29:16.280
Or at least parts of me do.

29:16.290 --> 29:17.380
You know what I mean?

29:17.390 --> 29:20.300
You lived at 224 Green Gates Crescent?

29:20.310 --> 29:22.190
Yeah,just a few blocks from here.

29:22.200 --> 29:24.460
- It backed onto a swamp.
- Yeah.

29:24.470 --> 29:26.900
I was scared of that
swamp as a little girl.

29:26.910 --> 29:28.630
How well did you know Roger Dillon?

29:28.640 --> 29:31.340
Oh,I don't know. He was my math tutor.

29:31.350 --> 29:36.870
And,well,math wasn't really my thing,so
I needed a lot of help,and,well...

29:36.880 --> 29:39.160
he kind of developed a crush on me.

29:39.170 --> 29:42.260
He was actually kind of cute
in a non-jock way,you know?

29:42.270 --> 29:43.680
Sweet.

29:43.690 --> 29:45.310
Oh,he loved The Cure.

29:45.320 --> 29:46.030
For what?

29:46.040 --> 29:48.080
- What did he have?
- It's a band,Bones.

29:48.090 --> 29:50.670
It's... It's... It's a band.

29:51.640 --> 29:53.600
Um,did he tutor you at your place?

29:53.610 --> 29:55.910
My place or the library.
Usually my place.

29:55.920 --> 29:57.660
I think he liked it there.

29:57.670 --> 29:59.610
You know,his own place wasn't very nice.

29:59.620 --> 30:03.730
Do you rember seeing
him on,uh,June 14,1987?

30:03.740 --> 30:04.620
Mom?

30:04.870 --> 30:05.950
Uh,I'm in here,honey.

30:05.960 --> 30:08.080
It would have been
the last day of school.

30:08.380 --> 30:09.570
I'm going to Pete's.

30:09.580 --> 30:10.400
Okay.

30:10.410 --> 30:11.420
What's going on?

30:11.430 --> 30:13.030
Um,these people are with the FBI.

30:13.040 --> 30:15.700
They're investigating
the time capsule murder.

30:15.710 --> 30:16.760
Nothing to worry about.

30:16.770 --> 30:19.840
Your parents were just
friends of the victim.

30:19.850 --> 30:21.500
- Well,that sucks.
- Yeah.

30:21.510 --> 30:23.440
Honey,why don't you go to Pete's?

30:29.210 --> 30:30.960
If you're going to be
late,just give me a call,

30:30.970 --> 30:32.620
'cause you have your cell phone,right?

30:32.630 --> 30:34.620
- I have it.
- Okay.

30:34.820 --> 30:35.770
What are you doing?

30:35.780 --> 30:37.560
- See you later,Mom.
- Okay.

30:38.400 --> 30:43.040
You know,I-I think I actually did
see Roger on the last day of school.

30:43.050 --> 30:43.740
Why?

30:43.750 --> 30:45.090
Like I said,he was my tutor.

30:45.100 --> 30:47.360
Why would he come to your
house on the last day of school?

30:47.370 --> 30:48.950
Honestly?

30:49.630 --> 30:52.620
He brought me my graded final,but
he'd have used any excuse.

30:52.630 --> 30:54.850
I didn't encourage him,but...

30:56.400 --> 31:00.150
High school was so long ago,and
none of us is the same person.

31:01.430 --> 31:05.470
I'm sorry Roger ended up that
way,but after he dropped off my final,

31:05.480 --> 31:07.960
I never saw him again,so...

31:09.430 --> 31:12.880
- Thank you,Ms. Stinson.
- Oh,yes.Uh-huh,of course.

31:15.430 --> 31:18.900
Could you please call up Terry
Stinson from the Foothill yearbook?

31:20.990 --> 31:25.730
Track team,Vice President of the Student
Council,runner up for Mr. Popularity.

31:25.740 --> 31:27.040
Where does it say that?

31:27.050 --> 31:28.630
It's the type,sweetie.

31:28.640 --> 31:30.660
He's Mr. Second Best.

31:30.670 --> 31:34.220
It's kind of like when you want Brad
Pitt and you get Matthew McConnaghey.

31:34.230 --> 31:36.670
And pull up the photo of his son,Alex.

31:36.680 --> 31:41.300
Alex Stinson shows three classic
examples of Mendelian inheritance.

31:41.310 --> 31:45.990
A cheek dimple on the left
side,cleft chin and detached earlobes.

31:46.000 --> 31:47.660
Distinct facial features.

31:47.670 --> 31:50.730
Wide set eyes,asymmetrical nostrils.

31:50.740 --> 31:52.650
Just like his dad.

31:52.660 --> 31:54.830
It's nothing like his dad.

31:57.080 --> 31:58.680
Oh,boy.

31:58.960 --> 32:03.630
Could you please replace Terry
Stinson with Roger Dillon?

32:06.800 --> 32:08.400
Oh,boy.

32:09.520 --> 32:14.590
20 years ago,Terry Stinson finds out that
Roger Dillon has sex with his girlfriend.

32:14.600 --> 32:16.360
And he kills him.

32:23.690 --> 32:25.240
e we'll take a DNA test.

32:25.250 --> 32:28.580
You realize in a murder
investigation,we can't rule anything out.

32:28.830 --> 32:33.090
Did you know that it was possible
that Alex was not your biological son?

32:33.100 --> 32:34.350
What?

32:38.240 --> 32:40.800
- Is it possible?
- Is it?

32:42.320 --> 32:46.010
Can I answer that after the DNA test?

32:49.180 --> 32:50.760
I guess I just did.

32:50.770 --> 32:52.280
So you didn't know?

32:52.290 --> 32:53.480
Terry didn't know.

32:53.490 --> 32:58.730
Alex was born on January 7,1988.

32:59.150 --> 33:01.020
I don't believe this.

33:02.950 --> 33:05.720
That means you were pregnant
in the spring already.

33:05.730 --> 33:09.140
You just wanted me to believe
that the baby was mine?

33:09.150 --> 33:10.960
No,no.

33:11.630 --> 33:15.050
I wanted... the baby
inside me to be yours.

33:15.060 --> 33:16.460
I don't get this.

33:16.470 --> 33:19.100
Roger-- what...
but he was...

33:20.260 --> 33:22.090
Why did you sleep with Roger?

33:22.100 --> 33:24.020
He was sweet. He was...

33:24.030 --> 33:25.870
I knew he was nuts about me.

33:25.880 --> 33:27.670
I liked feeling special.

33:27.680 --> 33:30.520
Let's face it,Terry,back
then,you were that guy.

33:30.530 --> 33:31.740
What guy?

33:31.750 --> 33:33.520
The guy who did anything he wanted.

33:33.530 --> 33:35.670
You didn't need me.

33:38.830 --> 33:40.500
Roger,he came over that day.

33:40.510 --> 33:42.790
He came through the
swamp. He was filthy.

33:42.800 --> 33:43.950
His father had just beaten him up...

33:43.960 --> 33:47.410
Ms. Stinson,did you tell Roger
that he had gotten you pregnant?

33:48.980 --> 33:50.410
Yes.

33:51.130 --> 33:52.390
He wanted to marry me.

33:52.400 --> 33:55.540
He said he could get the money
for us to go away together,

33:55.550 --> 33:57.590
but I told him I didn't want to.

33:57.600 --> 34:00.300
I was back with you by then.

34:00.310 --> 34:02.160
Only you.

34:03.400 --> 34:05.000
Why didn't you tell me?

34:05.010 --> 34:07.060
When I told you I was
pregnant,you were so happy.

34:07.070 --> 34:08.469
That's when I knew that you loved me.

34:08.480 --> 34:11.070
That you weren't "that guy."

34:11.080 --> 34:14.260
We could have a great
life together and we did.

34:14.270 --> 34:15.360
I'm sorry.

34:15.370 --> 34:17.510
I had to borrow one of your pictures.

34:17.520 --> 34:18.520
You stole that.

34:18.530 --> 34:20.290
What did you think happened to Roger?

34:20.300 --> 34:21.110
I don't know.

34:21.120 --> 34:22.650
He had the money.

34:22.659 --> 34:23.639
He was never happy here.

34:23.650 --> 34:27.670
I figured that he just
took off by himself.

34:30.280 --> 34:32.520
I am so sorry.

34:33.360 --> 34:36.570
I always wanted to tell
you the truth,but I just...

34:37.120 --> 34:42.239
I just couldn't figure out how to
tell you that Alex wasn't yours.

34:46.730 --> 34:48.739
Alex is my son.

34:50.659 --> 34:52.739
We are a family.

35:02.850 --> 35:05.530
Well,the murder happened at night
on a high school playing field,

35:05.540 --> 35:07.660
not a likely place to find adults.

35:07.670 --> 35:12.380
Plus,teenagers are dominated by their
ids,which make them act irrationally.

35:12.390 --> 35:16.220
Physiologically,their judgment's
impaired by an incomplete frontal lobe.

35:16.230 --> 35:18.530
You're what,22,right?

35:18.540 --> 35:20.430
How's your front lobe?

35:20.860 --> 35:22.120
Almost there?

35:22.520 --> 35:23.720
Again,a hectoring tone.

35:24.710 --> 35:26.280
All right,look,I'm
sorry,just keep going.

35:26.290 --> 35:28.160
All right,there was no
sexual assault,no theft.

35:28.170 --> 35:30.420
The watch and other
effects were still on him.

35:30.430 --> 35:33.120
Further indications that this
was just a rash and youthful act.

35:33.130 --> 35:34.710
Right,right. That's good for a kid.

35:34.720 --> 35:35.800
This is guess work,Booth.

35:35.810 --> 35:38.200
It's a logical interpretation
of subjective analysis

35:38.210 --> 35:41.700
by a highly intelligent
expert in his field,actually.

35:42.470 --> 35:46.140
The killer knew the exact date the time capsule
would be opened when he put the victim in there.

35:46.150 --> 35:49.230
He's been waiting 20 years
for that body to be found

35:49.240 --> 35:51.960
so he could reconcile
himself with his past,

35:51.970 --> 35:53.440
and finally pay for his crime.

35:53.450 --> 35:55.370
Like Terry Stinson?

35:55.380 --> 35:56.710
No.

35:58.050 --> 36:01.470
I think you're looking for someone
who's been punishing himself for years.

36:01.480 --> 36:04.420
Someone self-destructive,working
far below his potential.

36:04.430 --> 36:05.730
Then why doesn't he just confess?

36:05.740 --> 36:08.510
Most likely he has in
some way,Agent Booth.

36:08.520 --> 36:10.650
The question is,were you listening?

36:10.660 --> 36:13.170
Agent Booth is an
incredibly good listener.

36:13.180 --> 36:15.380
Yeah,I really am. It's my strength.

36:16.870 --> 36:21.500
Then perhaps the time capsule was just
a convenient place to stash a body.

36:21.740 --> 36:24.110
You know,profiling's
not an exact science.

36:24.120 --> 36:26.120
But I hope I'm right.

36:26.130 --> 36:29.390
I really want to tell my girlfriend
I helped catch a murderer.

36:29.980 --> 36:32.020
It'd be a good night for me.

36:37.000 --> 36:40.960
The textural stain on the undersurface
of Roger's mandible was liquid petroleum.

36:40.970 --> 36:41.810
An oil product?

36:41.820 --> 36:42.560
I know. I know.

36:42.570 --> 36:43.840
Dead common,right?

36:43.850 --> 36:45.660
But I did some further analysis.

36:45.670 --> 36:49.580
I found that there were microscopic particles
of granite embedded in the petroleum.

36:49.590 --> 36:52.220
Also,all over the broken
seal to the time capsule.

36:52.230 --> 36:54.180
Definitely not John Adamson's ice skate.

36:54.190 --> 36:56.320
Yeah,not unless he skated on asphalt.

36:56.330 --> 37:00.120
20 years ago what I'm seeing
as petroleum was asphalt.

37:00.130 --> 37:03.210
It was driven into Roger's
bone with a flat,metal...

37:03.220 --> 37:05.530
- An asphalt shovel?
- Yeah.

37:06.060 --> 37:08.580
Gil Bates worked paving driveways.

37:11.630 --> 37:13.710
Roger was my best friend.

37:13.720 --> 37:15.690
Gruff and Grim,right?

37:15.780 --> 37:17.390
Who was who?

37:17.900 --> 37:19.600
I was Gruff. Roger was Grim.

37:19.610 --> 37:23.940
So you went out to the field that night
to plant the yearbook in the time capsule.

37:23.950 --> 37:26.420
Right,surprise everyone
20 years down the line.

37:26.430 --> 37:30.500
You dug up the capsule and you broke
the seal with the asphalt shovel.

37:31.550 --> 37:34.000
Your amigo,Grim,wanted his money back?

37:34.010 --> 37:36.400
The money that you
earmarked for your business,

37:36.410 --> 37:38.860
all those computers that
were going to make you rich.

37:38.870 --> 37:40.000
And you couldn't do that,Gruff.

37:40.010 --> 37:42.420
You just couldn't give
Grim back the money.

37:42.430 --> 37:43.730
Could you stop using those names?

37:43.740 --> 37:45.420
Did he tell you that it
was for Janelle Brown?

37:45.430 --> 37:47.330
I bet he did.I bet old Grim said,

37:47.340 --> 37:50.570
"You know what,I'm sorry,Gruff,but
there's this girl. Our plans,they're dust."

37:50.580 --> 37:51.990
I asked you to just
stop using the names.

37:52.000 --> 37:54.300
You know,but then Grim
said,"My dream has changed. "

37:54.310 --> 37:57.630
- You and me,Gruff and Grim,we're finished."
- Stop it!

37:57.640 --> 37:59.180
You don't know what
you're talking about!

37:59.190 --> 38:00.450
We don't know what?

38:03.490 --> 38:06.670
Did he tell you it was
because she was pregnant?

38:09.650 --> 38:11.540
He should've told you.

38:11.550 --> 38:13.330
You would have understood.

38:13.340 --> 38:14.830
Understood what?

38:14.840 --> 38:18.270
Janelle was pregnant with Roger's son.

38:18.910 --> 38:20.480
Oh,my God.

38:22.040 --> 38:23.540
He didn't say.

38:23.550 --> 38:25.760
He just said that he loved her.

38:26.330 --> 38:29.650
I told him... I told
him how stupid that was.

38:30.060 --> 38:32.770
I said that she'd never look
at someone like him and...

38:32.780 --> 38:36.260
he got all pissed and then he hit me.

38:36.670 --> 38:39.740
And I just,I went and I picked
up the shovel and I just...

38:41.290 --> 38:43.560
I just jabbed.

38:46.970 --> 38:50.550
It was an accident. It was just a jab.

38:51.510 --> 38:52.920
He held his neck.

38:52.930 --> 38:55.450
And he went all white.

38:56.800 --> 39:00.450
The wound severed both his
jugular and his carotid.

39:00.460 --> 39:02.630
He would have died quickly.

39:02.640 --> 39:03.850
He did.

39:03.860 --> 39:08.070
I... I held him and
I told him I was sorry.

39:08.080 --> 39:10.740
He knew that I didn't mean it.

39:12.740 --> 39:15.160
I loved the guy.

39:18.240 --> 39:20.420
He has a kid?

39:21.580 --> 39:22.960
Yes.

39:22.970 --> 39:27.170
I hope I get the chance to
tell him about his father.

39:40.100 --> 39:42.820
All right,there was
this kid,uh,junior year.

39:42.830 --> 39:47.020
Okay,is this going to be another story
where you think you were humiliated,

39:47.030 --> 39:48.160
but you actually were not?

39:48.170 --> 39:49.160
Just listen to me.

39:49.170 --> 39:52.070
This kid,junior year,Harlan Kinney.

39:52.080 --> 39:56.610
He was one of those real
weird,you know,looking kids.

39:56.620 --> 39:59.710
He had this big Adam's
apple sticking out.

39:59.720 --> 40:01.840
And he wore his dad's clothes to school.

40:01.850 --> 40:04.290
You know,with the whole
stretchy belt around his waist.

40:04.300 --> 40:05.650
What's wrong with that? It's practical.

40:05.660 --> 40:06.920
You're not listening.

40:06.930 --> 40:10.650
He was one of those real superior type,

40:10.660 --> 40:12.880
always talking out of a thesaurus.

40:12.890 --> 40:15.590
And one day he came up to
me and a bunch of my buddies

40:15.600 --> 40:17.840
and he called us a bunch of Philistines.

40:17.850 --> 40:18.870
You know what that means,right?

40:18.880 --> 40:21.860
Yeah. A Philistine is
a smug,ignorant person

40:21.870 --> 40:25.080
who is antagonistic toward
higher thought and intelligence.

40:25.090 --> 40:27.360
Well,I didn't know what that
meant till I looked it up.

40:27.370 --> 40:31.360
I told Kinney,"Look,I'm not
Philistine,I'm Catholic."

40:34.570 --> 40:36.200
That's pretty close to humiliation.

40:36.210 --> 40:37.460
No,that's embarrassing.

40:37.470 --> 40:39.190
That's not the humiliating part.

40:40.230 --> 40:46.080
My buddy,picked Kinney up and
dangled him over the stairway.

40:47.260 --> 40:50.680
You know,he begged and
cried,and everyone laughed.

40:50.690 --> 40:52.800
How is this about you?

40:53.240 --> 40:54.790
I laughed.

40:56.370 --> 40:57.610
I don't understand.

40:57.620 --> 40:58.800
I could've stopped it.

40:58.810 --> 41:02.900
I could've stepped in and helped
the kid out. Instead I... I didn't.

41:04.210 --> 41:07.040
I chose my side,and
it was the wrong side.

41:07.760 --> 41:12.430
So you were humiliated because
you didn't act like a hero?

41:13.060 --> 41:14.910
Fine,fine,you know what?

41:14.920 --> 41:16.900
I'm perfect. My life was perfect.

41:16.910 --> 41:18.800
It's a good story,okay?

41:18.810 --> 41:20.340
But it's a bad one.

41:20.350 --> 41:23.730
I mean,it's both,I
guess. I mean,I get it.

41:24.010 --> 41:25.410
Yeah?

41:26.540 --> 41:28.030
What is that?

41:28.410 --> 41:29.790
Nothing.

41:30.620 --> 41:33.130
Well,you evolved.

41:33.140 --> 41:35.420
And evolution is very impressive.

41:35.430 --> 41:37.750
And that is definitely not nothing.

41:38.100 --> 41:39.270
This?

41:39.590 --> 41:41.320
- Did you bring that for me?
- No.

41:41.330 --> 41:43.520
Good,because it's the wrong Smurf.

41:43.530 --> 41:46.110
I liked Smurfette; that's Brainy Smurf.

41:46.120 --> 41:50.330
Smurfette was stupid,shallow
Smurf who only had her looks.

41:51.740 --> 41:53.790
Look,you're better than Smurfette.

41:53.800 --> 41:57.050
You have your looks
and a whole lot more.

42:00.750 --> 42:03.480
You did bring that for me to charm me

42:03.490 --> 42:06.850
in case I didn't find your
humiliation story impressive,

42:06.860 --> 42:09.110
but I did,so...

42:09.380 --> 42:11.670
So Ididimpressed you.

42:11.680 --> 42:14.280
That's what "impressive" means,dummy.

42:14.870 --> 42:16.350
You're such a Philistine.

42:16.360 --> 42:17.560
I'll tell you what.

42:17.570 --> 42:22.540
You can hold on to this,and it
will remind you how far I've come.

42:26.960 --> 42:29.190
I forgive you for snorting,Booth.

42:29.200 --> 42:32.440
Evolution is a long,long process.

42:32.450 --> 42:34.790
It takes hundreds of years.

42:35.210 --> 42:36.840
Thousands.

42:37.260 --> 42:39.980
Why do you have to always correct me?

42:40.890 --> 42:43.580
To help you evolve.

